data.name: Indena
data.description:
Since 1921 we’ve been taking inspiration from Nature with scientific advancements. Bright minds come together at Indena to support human health toward a new, healthier future. Our expertise has always been creating phytochemical solutions that are versatile and timeless - evolving with people's changing needs - with high quality, reliability, traceability and integrity.


The R&D department is Indena’s internal think tank dedicated to phytochemical engineering as a means to explore how humankind, in the next few decades, might take care of its health by reconnecting with the natural world.


Nature offers us boundless inspiration for brilliant ideas. There is no limit to what we can achieve when research begins with better, smarter cooperation with Nature itself, in a never-ending story of quality.


We care about where plants are grown, about how they are handled and for the people who are responsible for them along the supply chain. We know that paying attention at every step of the way positively impacts the quality and effectiveness we can offer.


The company owns 100 patent families, has published more than 1000 scientific studies and cooperates with the world’s most prestigious universities and private research institutions. Indena employs over 900 staff, investing a significant amount of its annual turnover in research, making this activity the key to its success.


Headquartered in Milan, Indena has 4 production sites and 5 international branches throughout the world and manages sales in more than 80 countries. The company's experts communicate and interact constantly with the major international regulatory authorities and cooperate on the update of all the main pharmacopeias.

data.name: Quercefit
data.description: Quercefit® is the patent-pending food-grade delivery system of quercetin from Sophora japonica L., formulated with Phytosome® proprietary technology to optimize the biological absorption of the flavonoids, supporting overall wellbeing in many conditions. Compared to the unformulated quercetin, bioabsorption and solubility are greatly optimized so that lower dosages can be used, while still retaining its efficacy.

data.name: Berbevis
data.description: Berbevis® is an innovative, food-grade ingredient that is based on the formulation of berberine from the roots of Berberis aristata. It sports a new custom Phytosome® formulation, optimizing the bioabsorption by 10-folds. Berbevis® might promote a healthy metabolism by positively modulating blood sugar levels in a plethora of multifactorial disorders, including type II diabetes and PCOS.

data.name: Meriva
data.description: Meriva® is a patent-pending delivery form of curcumin and has been shown to improve the bioavailability of curcuminoids by up to 30-fold compared to traditional forms. Studies have demonstrated that Meriva® can reduce stiffness, muscle soreness, improve physical function, and promote liver health and overall quality of life. Additionally, a long-term study has shown Meriva® to support ocular health and confirm its excellent safety profile.

data.name: Prodigest
data.description: Prodigest® is a combination of two standardized ingredients: a lipophilic CO2 extract of ginger roots (Zingiber officinale Rosc.) and a unique extract of artichoke leaves (Cynara cardunculus L.) that has been shown to improve digestion. Digestive problems can ruin the pleasure of a good meal, but Prodigest® offers a new, natural way to enjoy healthy digestion. This unique combination of artichoke leaves and ginger extracts from Indena has been proven effective.

data.name: Relissa
data.description: Relissa„¢ is not your typical lemon balm ingredient. It is a standardized extract of Melissa officinalis leaves with a high content of hydroxycinnamic and rosmarinic acid, combined with an innovative formulative technology. The unique combination of high and standardized content of hydroxycinnamic and rosmarinic acid, along with the innovative formulative technology, sets Relissa„¢ apart from other lemon balm extracts.

data.name: Centevita
data.description: Centevita® is a dry extract obtained from the leaves of Centella asiatica (L.) Urban. This product is used in the nutraceutical industry for its antioxidant activity. It contains more than 45% of the sum of asiaticoside, madecassoside, and asiatic and madecassic acids, as determined by HPLC. This product is ECOCERT- and COSMOS-validated.

data.name: Mitidol
data.description: Mitidol® is a formulation of two standardized botanical extracts, Zingiber officinale and Acmella oleracea, that are effective as a natural adjuvant in pain management. Ginger, or Zingiber officinale Roscoe, is an excellent source of several bioactive phenolics, including non-volatile pungent compounds such as gingerols, paradols, shogaols, and zingerones. These compounds have major properties that include immune modulatory, anti-inflammatory, anti-tumorigenic, anti-hyperglycemic, and antilipidemic actions.

data.name: Vazguard
data.description: Vazguard® is a standardized extract from Bergamot - Citrus bergamia Risso et Poiteau, exclusively sourced from a specific part of Southern Italy, in the Phytosome® form. It is effective thanks to the power of its unique mix of polyphenols and, in particular, a high concentration of flavonoids found in bergamot juice, albedo, and flavedo.

data.name: Enovita
data.description: Enovita® is a proprietary proanthocyanidin-rich (OPC) extract made exclusively with grape seeds from white wine production. Using only water as the extraction solvent, Enovita® is a food-grade grape seed extract whose development has capitalized on Indena's 40-year experience in grape seed extract production.

data.name: Lymphaselect®
data.description: Lymphaselect® is a standardized dry extract obtained from the aerial parts of Melilotus officinalis (L.), a plant known as Yellow Sweet Clover or King’s Clover, a name related to its alleged use by Henry VIII. Sweet clover has been traditionally used in the treatment of venous-lymphatic insufficiencies.

data.name: Indena Silymarin
data.description: Indena Silymarin is a dry extract obtained from the fruit without pappum of Silybum marianum (L.) Gaertn. This product is used in pharmaceuticals and nutraceuticals for its benefits in antioxidant activity and healthy liver. This product is kosher-certified. It falls under the broad category of liver health and liver diseases, as well as antioxidant capacity.

data.name: Indena Saw Palmetto CO₂
data.description: Indena Saw Palmetto CO₂ is an oily or soft extract obtained from the fruit of Serenoa repens (Bartr.) Small. This product is used in various pharmaceutical applications for its benefits in promoting urinary tract health, prostate health, and its antiandrogen and anti-BPH properties.

data.name: Mitidol®
data.description: Mitidol® is a formulation of two standardized botanical extracts, Zingiber officinale and Acmella oleracea, that are effective as a natural adjuvant in pain management. Ginger, or Zingiber officinale Roscoe, is an excellent source of several bioactive phenolics, including non-volatile pungent compounds such as gingerols, paradols, shogaols, and zingerones. These compounds have major properties that include immune modulatory, anti-inflammatory, anti-tumorigenic, anti-hyperglycemic, and antilipidemic actions.

data.name: Indena Devil’s Claw 100% procumbens
data.description: Indena Devil’s Claw 100% procumbens is a dry extract obtained from the root of Harpagophytum procumbens DC. This product is used in nutraceuticals for its benefits in joint health, and it is halal-certified. It is composed of 1.8-2.2% of harpagoside, as determined by HPLC.

data.name: Greenselect® Phytosome®
data.description: Greenselect® Phytosome® is a proprietary, caffeine-free catechin extract from green tea formulated with Phytosome® technology. Traditionally, green tea consumption has been linked to lower body fat. Clinical studies have also demonstrated that green tea increases thermogenesis, which is the production of body heat derived from fat oxidation, thus promoting energy expenditure and caloric consumption. There are two independent human studies which support the beneficial effects of Greenselect® Phytosome® on weight management and general health when associated with diet.

data.name: Indena Centella asiatica
data.description: Indena Centella asiatica is a dry extract that is obtained from the leaves of Centella asiatica (L.) Urban. This product is used in the pharmaceutical industry as an anti-wrinkle and stretch mark improver. As determined by HPLC, it contains 36 - 44% asiaticoside and 56 - 64% genins as the sum of asiatic acid and madecassic acid.

data.name: Indena Linden Tree
data.description: Indena Linden Tree is a dry extract obtained from the inflorescence of Tilia cordata Mill. /Tilia platyphyllos Scop. This product is used in pharmaceuticals and nutraceuticals for its benefits in antioedema, healthy mood, and spasmolytic. Indena Linden Tree is kosher-certified.

data.name: Indena Artichoke
data.description: Indena Artichoke is a dry extract obtained from the leaves of Cynara cardunculus L. This product is used in the nutraceuticals industry for its benefits for cholesterol and intestinal health. It contains 6 - 12% of caffeoylquinic acids, as calculated by HPLC. This product is halal- and kosher-certified.

data.description: Ginkgo biloba EUR. PH. is a dry extract obtained from the leaves of Ginkgo biloba L. This product is used in the pharmaceutical industry for its benefits in blood circulation health. It is CEP granted and contains more than 22.0% less than 27.0% of flavonoids, more than 2.6% less than 3.2% of bilobalide, more than 2.8% less than 3.4% of ginkgolides A,B,C, and less than 5.0 ppm of ginkgolic acids by HPLC.

data.name: Ginkgo biloba HF
data.description: Ginkgo biloba HF is an ethanolic extract obtained from the leaves of Ginkgo biloba L. This product is used in the Nutraceutical industry for its benefits in antioxidant activity, cognition, and circulation health. This product is halal-certified. It falls under the broad categories of antioxidants and brain health function.
